      <txt c="X" a="X" r="X" s="2" w="850" x="40" y="80" delay="0" pt="1" e="-3" align="left">If a Captain gives some bottles of alcohol to the Customs authorities, in order to gain business advantages to which he/she would not otherwise be entitled.

How would that be considered?</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="200" delay="0" crct="49" align="left">A bribe</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="260" delay="0" crct="25" align="left">A facilitation payment</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="320" delay="0" crct="70" align="left">Business as usual, not a criminal offence</txt>
